<section id="actionClickLocator" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                     xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                     xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <?dbhtml dir="clickLocator"?>
  <title>Click Locator</title>
 
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Use this action to click an item based on its locator.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        The action requires no component name and no object mapping - the component 
        in your AUT is found based on the locator you enter.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        You can use different types of locators, and can find out the locator for 
        your component using website inspection tools.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
</section>